I have family visiting from out of town. He collects Hard Rock pins, and wanted to purchase one. We got there right as they opened, and they were setting up for a private party, which they told us would last for about three and a half hours. I would understand if the private party had started already - clearly somebody paid a lot of money to rent out the entire restaurant, so good on them. But since it hadn't started and all we wanted was to pop in and buy some merchandise, that seemed like something that could reasonably be accommodated. Instead, we basically got a condescending "Yeah, no" from the very disinterested employee who clearly didn't care at all. I certainly hope he turns on his positive attitude for the private party.

