It's 5:48 on Sunday, December 27th. Just got done eating a plate of pork with the sweet and spicy mixed barbecue, Parmesan fries and 7 cheese baked mac and cheese, with sweet tea to drink. The fries were great, and were the "worst" thing on my plate - by a wide margin. My fiancé got the glazed cornbread, which was spectacular. We were greeted and welcomed in, asked if it was our first time, and then given a walk through of the menu. The lady taking our order was really sweet. The guy who brought out the food was pleasant, and had a good conversation with us. Our enjoyment was confirmed multiple times. The best part was, the owner must have heard us talking about their special, smoked chicken noodle soup, because shortly after talking about it he brought a sample out for us. It was (like everything we ate) delicious... But the service was somehow better than the food.

