beZHJxW4bdX-8gh61VgMJg
My fiancé and I just tried this place after looking for a new place to try on Yelp. We got there right as they opened, so it was a little disorganized (no ice in the soda machine yet), but it really wasn't a big deal. The first thing I noticed was paper towel rolls on the table - immediately making me trust this place as a BBQ restaurant. I enjoyed the BBQ salsa with chips, the home style cornbread was fantastic. We tried a couple side, even ones we knew weren't really things we typically enjoyed (baked beans and macaroni salad)... The beans were ok, and we just aren't fans of cold pasta. I think they'd probably be fantastic to people who enjoy those sides, and knowing that I don't typically like baked beans and she doesn't like cold pasta, I'm not going to hold that against them. The sandwiches? Wow. I got the Chicago Fire and she got the Baltimore classic. Mine had pico and chipotle BBQ sauce, and hers had potato salad. First of all, there was so much meat, it went from a sandwich to a sandwich and half a plate. It was messy, just like it's supposed to be. Taste wise it was out of this world. We tried a sample of their sauces, and I particularly enjoyed the chipotle. We will definitely be back.

